text: Jack Eduardo Jean Baptiste Cruz (born 20 December 1999) is a Honduran footballer who plays as a midfielder for C.D. Real de Minas on loan from F.C. Motagua. ==Career== The midfielder was promoted to the first team after playing on the Motague U-19 team in January 2018. Baptiste joined Loudoun United on loan for the rest of 2019.LOUDOUN UNITED FC SIGN MIDFIELDERS JACK JEAN BAPTISTE AND ARIEL FANTONI, loudoununitedfc.com, 3 May 2019 ==References== ==External links== *USL profile Category:1999 births Category:Living people Category:Honduran footballers Category:Honduran expatriate footballers Category:Association football midfielders Category:F.C.
